commitResults.messageTitle: Apply Checkstyle fixes to all classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Correct all Checkstyle violations across the project to ensure the code
follows the agreed style guidelines. These changes improve code readability
and maintain consistency throughout the codebase.

Key changes include:
- Reformatted code to adhere to line length limits
- Fixed missing Javadoc comments
- Adjusted spacing and indentation
- Resolved naming convention issues

These improvements help maintain clean, readable code and reduce potential
style-related errors during future development.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add duplicate detection feature I ntroduce functionality to detect and prevent duplicate tasks when users attempt to add the same task multiple times.
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, the system allowed duplicate tasks, which could lead
to redundancy and confusion for the user. This change enhances
the user experience by checking for duplicate task descriptions
before adding a new task to the task list.

Changes made:
- Added a `isDuplicate()` method in TaskList to check if a task
  with the same description already exists.
- Modified `AddCommand` to prevent adding duplicate tasks and
  provide feedback to the user if a duplicate is detected.
- Updated `Ui` class to display a message when a duplicate task
  is detected.
